              <h1>Employers</h1>
              <p> In addition to the 
                service we provide to students, graduates and academics, our Career 
                Development Centre offers the following advice and services to 
                employers and recruiters: 
              <ul>
                <li>Advice and guidance on degree courses relevant to your requirements</li>
            <li>Contact with tutors on courses which you may want to target</li>
            <li>Access to the resources held in the Careers Information Room</li>
            <li>Interviewing facilities</li>
            <li>Arrange Employer Presentations and Recruitment Visits</li>
          </ul>
              <p><span class="U">Advertising 
                Vacancies</span><br />
                <br />
                From March 2007, our service is participating in a shared vacancy 
                system which will allow employers to advertise and promote graduate 
                vacancies to students across Scotland.&nbsp; You will be given 
                the opportunity to decide where to advertise - to students at 
                Abertay ONLY or/and with other participating universities.&nbsp; 
                You can also use this facility to advertise work experience placements 
                - at present, these are not shared.&nbsp; Employers will need 
                to register to use the service.&nbsp; </p>
                            <p style="margin-top: 0;"><font color="#FF0000" size="3"><a href="http://abertay.prospectsnet.com"><span style="background-color: #FFFF00">CLICK 
                HERE TO REGISTER AND SUBMIT YOUR VACANCY</span></a> </font></p>
              <p>If you are experiencing 
                any problems using this facility please <a href="ContactUs.cfm?CKey=013">contact 
                us</a>.</p>
                            <p>The <a href="http://www.agcasscotland.org.uk" target="_blank">AGCAS Scotland website</a>
            offers information to graduate recruiters, including labour market
            information, details of events and graduate fairs. A <a href="http://www.agcasscotland.org.uk/employers/guide.htm" target="_blank">Guide
            to Scottish Higher Education</a> is also available on this website
            explaining the distinctive features of Scottish secondary and higher
            education.</p>
              <p>If you are looking to 
                submit details of any part-time, seasonal or casual vacancies 
                please see <a href="http://www.abertay.ac.uk/scope">the Abertay Jobshop </a> 
                for further details. </p>
              </p>
          <div class="Top"><a href="#Frm" class="TopLink" title="Return to the top">Top</a></div>
